a unique opportunity.

132
00:13:12.458 --> 00:13:15.002 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[mooing]

133
00:13:15.085 --> 00:13:17.713 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>We invented farming.</i>

134
00:13:20.633 --> 00:13:25.554 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>We learnt how to exploit the seasons</i>
<i>to produce food crops.</i>

135
00:13:27.431 --> 00:13:31.477 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>The history of</i>
<i>all human civilization followed.</i>

136
00:13:33.395 --> 00:13:37.107 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Each generation able</i>
<i>to develop and progress</i>

137
00:13:37.191 --> 00:13:40.694 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>only because the living world</i>
<i>could be relied upon</i>

138
00:13:40.778 --> 00:13:43.239 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>to deliver us the conditions we needed.</i>

139
00:13:46.575 --> 00:13:51.664 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>The pace of progress was unlike anything</i>
<i>to be found in the fossil record.</i>

140
00:13:54.917 --> 00:13:59.463 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Our intelligence changed the way
in which we evolved.

141
00:14:00.256 --> 00:14:01.549 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
In the past,

142
00:14:01.632 --> 00:14:07.721 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
animals had to develop some
physical ability to change their lives.

143
00:14:08.514 --> 00:14:11.809 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But for us, an idea could do that.

144
00:14:11.892 --> 00:14:15.938 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And the idea could be passed
from one generation to the next.

145
00:14:18.524 --> 00:14:22.069 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>We were transforming</i>
<i>what a species could achieve.</i>

146
00:14:26.323 --> 00:14:32.580 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
A few millennia after this began,
I grew up at exactly the right moment.

147
00:14:35.040 --> 00:14:37.793 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>The start of my career in my 20s</i>

148
00:14:37.877 --> 00:14:41.964 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>coincided with the advent</i>
<i>of global air travel.</i>

149
00:14:43.507 --> 00:14:46.969 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>So, I had the privilege of being</i>
<i>amongst the first</i>

150
00:14:47.052 --> 00:14:51.223 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>to fully experience the bounty of life</i>
<i>that had come about</i>

151
00:14:51.307 --> 00:14:53.893 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>as a result of</i>
<i>the Holocene's gentle climate.</i>

152
00:15:14.079 --> 00:15:17.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Wherever I went, there was wilderness.</i>

153
00:15:18.459 --> 00:15:20.794 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Sparkling coastal seas.</i>

154
00:15:21.921 --> 00:15:23.547 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Vast forests.</i>

155
00:15:25.132 --> 00:15:27.134 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Immense grasslands.</i>

156
00:15:27.217 --> 00:15:31.180 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>You could fly for hours</i>
<i>over the untouched wilderness.</i>

157
00:15:33.933 --> 00:15:38.395 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>And there I was, actually being asked</i>
<i>to explore these places</i>

158
00:15:38.479 --> 00:15:42.107 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>and record the wonders</i>
<i>of the natural world for people back home.</i>

159
00:15:44.234 --> 00:15:45.736 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And to begin with, it was quite easy.

160
00:15:45.819 --> 00:15:48.238 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
People had never seen pangolins
before on television.

161
00:15:48.322 --> 00:15:50.032 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They'd never seen sloths before.

162
00:15:50.115 --> 00:15:52.326 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They had never seen the center
of New Guinea before.

163
00:15:58.123 --> 00:16:00.376 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>It was the best time of my life.</i>

164
00:16:01.627 --> 00:16:04.505 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The best time of our lives.

165
00:16:05.214 --> 00:16:09.426 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>The Second World War was over,</i>
<i>technology was making our lives easier.</i>

166
00:16:11.971 --> 00:16:15.724 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>The pace of change</i>
<i>was getting faster and faster.</i>

167
00:16:16.475 --> 00:16:18.477 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[indistinct chatter]

168
00:16:21.480 --> 00:16:24.650 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Attenborough] <i>It felt that nothing</i>
<i>would limit our progress.</i>

169
00:16:25.693 --> 00:16:28.779 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>The future was going to be exciting.</i>

170
00:16:28.862 --> 00:16:31.824 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>It was going to bring everything</i>
<i>we had ever dreamed of.</i>

171
00:16:34.910 --> 00:16:39.289 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This was before any of us were aware
that there were problems.

172
00:16:52.886 --> 00:16:57.391 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>My first visit to East Africa was in 1960.</i>

173
00:17:01.687 --> 00:17:06.900 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Back then, it seemed inconceivable</i>
<i>that we, a single species,</i>

174
00:17:06.984 --> 00:17:12.489 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>might one day have the power to threaten</i>
<i>the very existence of the wilderness.</i>

175
00:17:16.076 --> 00:17:20.664 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The Maasai word "Serengeti"
means "endless plains."

176
00:17:21.290 --> 00:17:24.001 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
To those who live here,
it's an apt description.

177
00:17:24.084 --> 00:17:26.754 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You can be in one spot on the Serengeti,

178
00:17:26.837 --> 00:17:29.506 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and the place is totally empty of animals,

179
00:17:29.590 --> 00:17:31.050 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and then, the next morning...

180
00:17:31.133 --> 00:17:32.593 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[bellowing]

181
00:17:32.676 --> 00:17:34.720 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>...one million wildebeest.</i>

182
00:17:34.803 --> 00:17:37.890 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[bellowing]

183
00:17:41.185 --> 00:17:43.437 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>A quarter of a million zebra.</i>

184
00:17:43.520 --> 00:17:46.023 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[snorting]

185
00:17:48.150 --> 00:17:49.943 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Half a million gazelle.</i>

186
00:17:53.030 --> 00:17:54.656 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>A few days after that...</i>

187
00:17:55.991 --> 00:17:59.328 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>and they're gone... over the horizon.</i>

188
00:17:59.411 --> 00:18:03.499 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>You can be forgiven for thinking</i>
<i>that these plains are endless</i>

189
00:18:04.083 --> 00:18:06.293 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
when they could swallow up such a herd.

190
00:18:07.377 --> 00:18:08.962 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>It took a visionary scientist,</i>

191
00:18:09.046 --> 00:18:12.716 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Bernhard Grzimek,</i>
<i>to explain that this wasn't true.</i>

192
00:18:16.011 --> 00:18:21.433 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>He and his son used a plane</i>
<i>to follow the herds over the horizon.</i>

193
00:18:22.059 --> 00:18:24.436 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[grunting]

194
00:18:31.610 --> 00:18:34.530 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>They charted them</i>
<i>as they moved across rivers,</i>

195
00:18:34.613 --> 00:18:37.783 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>through woodlands,</i>
<i>and over national borders.</i>

196
00:18:39.952 --> 00:18:42.371 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>They discovered that the Serengeti herds</i>

197
00:18:42.454 --> 00:18:47.376 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>required an enormous area</i>
<i>of healthy grassland to function.</i>

198
00:18:48.627 --> 00:18:52.965 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>That without such an immense space,</i>
<i>the herds would diminish</i>

199
00:18:53.048 --> 00:18:57.010 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>and the entire ecosystem</i>
<i>would come crashing down.</i>

200
00:18:58.804 --> 00:19:03.016 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The point for me was simple:
the wild is far from unlimited.

201
00:19:03.100 --> 00:19:06.019 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's finite. It needs protecting.

202
00:19:06.520 --> 00:19:10.149 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And a few years later,
that idea became obvious to everyone.

203
00:19:10.941 --> 00:19:16.488 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[NASA technician] <i>Five, four,</i>
<i>three, two one, zero.</i>

204
00:19:18.448 --> 00:19:23.162 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
[Attenborough] <i>I was in a television</i>
<i>studio when the Apollo mission launched.</i>

205
00:19:27.249 --> 00:19:28.625 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>It was the first time</i>

206
00:19:28.709 --> 00:19:32.421 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>that any human had moved away</i>
<i>far enough from the earth</i>

207
00:19:32.504 --> 00:19:34.339 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>to see the whole planet.</i>

208
00:19:35.716 --> 00:19:37.843 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>And this is what they saw...</i>

209
00:19:40.554 --> 00:19:42.514 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>what we all saw.</i>

210
00:19:43.932 --> 00:19:48.854 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Our planet, vulnerable and isolated.</i>

211
00:19:54.902 --> 00:19:59.489 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>One of the extraordinary things about it</i>
<i>was that the world</i>

212
00:19:59.573 --> 00:20:02.326 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
could actually watch it as it happened.

213
00:20:02.910 --> 00:20:09.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It was extraordinary that you could see
what a man out in space could see

214
00:20:09.124 --> 00:20:11.210 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
as he saw it at the same time.

215
00:20:12.628 --> 00:20:16.840 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And I remember very well that first shot.

216
00:20:17.341 --> 00:20:20.093 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You saw a blue marble,

217
00:20:20.177 --> 00:20:26.642 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
a blue sphere in the blackness,
and you realized that that was the earth.

218
00:20:27.142 --> 00:20:31.104 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And in that one shot, there was
the whole of humanity with nothing else

219
00:20:31.188 --> 00:20:35.734 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
except the person that was
in the spacecraft taking that picture.

220
00:20:36.735 --> 00:20:41.531 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And that completely changed
the mindset of the population,

221
00:20:41.615 --> 00:20:43.242 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
the human population of the world.

222
00:20:46.870 --> 00:20:48.997 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Our home was not limitless.</i>

223
00:20:50.624 --> 00:20:53.252 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>There was an edge to our existence.</i>

224
00:20:54.795 --> 00:20:59.049 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It was a rediscovery
of a fundamental truth.

225
00:21:00.259 --> 00:21:04.346 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We are ultimately bound by
and reliant upon

226
00:21:04.429 --> 00:21:07.641 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
the finite natural world about us.

227
00:21:09.559 --> 00:21:13.438 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>This truth defined the life we led</i>
<i>in our pre-history,</i>

228
00:21:13.522 --> 00:21:17.067 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>the time before farming and civilization.</i>

229
00:21:17.651 --> 00:21:20.862 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Even as some of us</i>
<i>were setting foot on the moon,</i>

230
00:21:20.946 --> 00:21:26.451 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>others were still leading such a life</i>
<i>in the most remote parts of the planet.</i>

231
00:21:34.042 --> 00:21:40.090 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>In 1971, I set out to find</i>
<i>an uncontacted tribe in New Guinea.</i>

232
00:21:43.719 --> 00:21:50.309 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>These people were hunter-gatherers,</i>
<i>as all humankind had been before farming.</i>

233
00:21:51.518 --> 00:21:53.812 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[speaking tribal language]

234
00:21:53.895 --> 00:21:57.691 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Attenborough] <i>They lived in small numbers</i>
<i>and didn't take too much.</i>

235
00:21:58.191 --> 00:22:02.029 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[speaking tribal language]

236
00:22:02.112 --> 00:22:04.448 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Attenborough] <i>They ate meat rarely.</i>

237
00:22:05.365 --> 00:22:09.911 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>The resources they used</i>
<i>naturally renewed themselves.</i>

238
00:22:10.871 --> 00:22:15.542 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Working with their traditional technology,</i>
<i>they were living sustainably,</i>

239
00:22:16.126 --> 00:22:20.005 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>a lifestyle that could continue</i>
<i>effectively forever.</i>

240
00:22:20.797 --> 00:22:23.467 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[speaking native language]

241
00:22:23.550 --> 00:22:26.303 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Attenborough] <i>It was a stark contrast</i>
<i>to the world I knew.</i>

242
00:22:27.471 --> 00:22:30.724 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>A world that demanded more every day.</i>

243
00:22:40.734 --> 00:22:44.988 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I spent the latter half of the 1970s
traveling the world,

244
00:22:45.072 --> 00:22:49.409 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
making a series I had long dreamed of
called <i>Life on Earth,</i>

245
00:22:50.577 --> 00:22:54.915 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>the story of the evolution of life</i>
<i>and its diversity.</i>

246
00:22:56.708 --> 00:22:59.002 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>It was shot in 39 countries.</i>

247
00:23:00.295 --> 00:23:03.673 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>We filmed 650 species,</i>

248
00:23:03.757 --> 00:23:07.177 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>and we traveled</i>
<i>one and a half million miles.</i>

249
00:23:07.844 --> 00:23:10.305 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>That's the sort of commitment you need</i>

250
00:23:10.388 --> 00:23:14.309 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>if you want to even begin</i>
<i>making a portrait of the living world.</i>

251
00:23:16.103 --> 00:23:17.395 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But it was noticeable

252
00:23:17.479 --> 00:23:20.649 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that some of these animals
were becoming harder to find.

253
00:23:36.748 --> 00:23:39.417 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>When I filmed with the mountain gorillas,</i>

254
00:23:39.501 --> 00:23:44.506 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>there were only 300 left</i>
<i>in a remote jungle in Central Africa.</i>

255
00:23:46.007 --> 00:23:48.426 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Baby gorillas were at a premium,

256
00:23:48.510 --> 00:23:51.721 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and poachers would kill
a dozen adults to get one.

257
00:23:53.473 --> 00:23:58.019 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I got as close as I did only because</i>
<i>the gorillas were used to people.</i>

258
00:24:00.313 --> 00:24:05.110 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>The only way to keep them alive</i>
<i>was for rangers to be with them every day.</i>

259
00:24:11.366 --> 00:24:16.580 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The process of extinction that I'd seen
as a boy... in the rocks,

260
00:24:17.581 --> 00:24:21.835 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I now became aware was happening
right there around me

261
00:24:22.627 --> 00:24:25.046 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
to animals with which I was familiar.

262
00:24:26.840 --> 00:24:28.550 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Our closest relatives.</i>

263
00:24:32.095 --> 00:24:34.097 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>And we were responsible.</i>

264
00:24:36.933 --> 00:24:39.477 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>It revealed a cold reality.</i>

265
00:24:40.937 --> 00:24:43.064 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Once a species became our target,

266
00:24:43.565 --> 00:24:47.068 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
there was now nowhere on earth
that it could hide.

267
00:24:59.748 --> 00:25:06.296 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Whales were being slaughtered by fleets</i>
<i>of industrial whaling ships in the 1970s.</i>

268
00:25:10.508 --> 00:25:13.678 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>The largest whales, the blues,</i>

269
00:25:13.762 --> 00:25:16.389 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>numbered only a few thousand by then.</i>

270
00:25:21.102 --> 00:25:23.730 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>They were virtually impossible to find.</i>

271
00:25:26.858 --> 00:25:32.197 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>We found humpbacks off Hawaii</i>
<i>only by listening out for their calls.</i>

272
00:25:32.781 --> 00:25:35.116 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
A moment ago, we made this recording

273
00:25:35.200 --> 00:25:39.120 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
with an underwater microphone
here in the Pacific near Hawaii.

274
00:25:39.204 --> 00:25:40.372 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Just listen to this.

275
00:25:41.998 --> 00:25:45.794 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[whales singing]

276
00:25:47.379 --> 00:25:49.381 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[whales continue singing]

277
00:25:52.342 --> 00:25:56.304 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Recordings like these revealed</i>
<i>that the songs of the humpbacks</i>

278
00:25:56.388 --> 00:25:58.515 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>are long and complex.</i>

279
00:25:59.849 --> 00:26:03.728 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Humpbacks living in the same area</i>
<i>learn their songs from each other.</i>

280
00:26:04.604 --> 00:26:10.277 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>And the songs have distinct themes</i>
<i>and variations which evolve over time.</i>

281
00:26:10.360 --> 00:26:13.238 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[whales singing]

282
00:26:19.327 --> 00:26:21.997 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Their mournful songs were the key</i>

283
00:26:22.080 --> 00:26:24.958 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>to transforming people's opinions</i>
<i>about them.</i>

284
00:26:27.002 --> 00:26:28.628 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[speaking Russian]

285
00:26:29.462 --> 00:26:32.215 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
