529
00:52:08.750 --> 00:52:11.294 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Within the span of the next lifetime,</i>

530
00:52:12.170 --> 00:52:15.423 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>the security and stability</i>
<i>of the Holocene,</i>

531
00:52:16.842 --> 00:52:18.927 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>our Garden of Eden...</i>

532
00:52:20.595 --> 00:52:21.930 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>will be lost.</i>

533
00:52:31.231 --> 00:52:37.237 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Right now, we're facing a manmade disaster
of global scale.

534
00:52:38.488 --> 00:52:40.907 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Our greatest threat in thousands of years.

535
00:52:41.908 --> 00:52:43.493 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If we don't take action,

536
00:52:44.077 --> 00:52:46.580 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
the collapse of our civilizations

537
00:52:47.330 --> 00:52:52.794 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and the extinction of much of
the natural world is on the horizon.

538
00:52:53.461 --> 00:52:55.088 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But the longer we leave it,

539
00:52:55.589 --> 00:52:59.092 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
the more difficult it'll be
to do something about it.

540
00:52:59.801 --> 00:53:01.720 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
And you could happily retire.

541
00:53:03.096 --> 00:53:09.561 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But you now want to explain to us
what peril we are in.

542
00:53:10.645 --> 00:53:11.897 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Um...

543
00:53:11.980 --> 00:53:17.527 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and, in a way, I wish I wasn't
involved in this struggle.

544
00:53:17.611 --> 00:53:18.612 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[chuckles]

545
00:53:18.695 --> 00:53:21.364 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Because I wish the struggle
wasn't there or necessary.

546
00:53:21.865 --> 00:53:26.119 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But I've had unbelievable luck
and good fortune.

547
00:53:26.620 --> 00:53:31.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Um, and I certainly
would feel very guilty...

548
00:53:32.626 --> 00:53:38.048 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
if I saw what the problems are
and decided to ignore them.

549
00:53:38.131 --> 00:53:39.633 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
[audience applauding]

550
00:53:41.259 --> 00:53:43.470 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
[Attenborough on video]
<i>Climbing over the tightly-packed bodies</i>

551
00:53:43.553 --> 00:53:45.889 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>is the only way across the crowd.</i>

552
00:53:45.972 --> 00:53:47.432 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[groaning]

553
00:53:47.515 --> 00:53:50.060 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Those beneath can get crushed to death.</i>

554
00:53:56.191 --> 00:53:57.317 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[walruses groaning]

555
00:54:07.494 --> 00:54:12.749 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Attenborough] <i>We are facing nothing less</i>
<i>than the collapse of the living world.</i>

556
00:54:14.584 --> 00:54:18.004 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>The very thing that gave birth</i>
<i>to our civilization.</i>

557
00:54:19.422 --> 00:54:23.718 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>The thing we rely upon</i>
<i>for every element of the lives we lead.</i>

558
00:54:27.055 --> 00:54:29.182 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>No one wants this to happen.</i>

559
00:54:29.849 --> 00:54:33.061 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>None of us can afford for it to happen.</i>

560
00:54:36.564 --> 00:54:38.400 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>So, what do we do?</i>

561
00:54:40.694 --> 00:54:42.404 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's quite straightforward.

562
00:54:43.363 --> 00:54:46.199 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's been staring us
in the face all along.

563
00:54:48.576 --> 00:54:50.870 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>To restore stability to our planet,</i>

564
00:54:51.788 --> 00:54:54.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>we must restore its biodiversity.</i>

565
00:54:56.751 --> 00:54:59.129 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>The very thing that we've removed.</i>

566
00:55:03.466 --> 00:55:07.470 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>It's the only way out of this crisis</i>
<i>we have created.</i>

567
00:55:10.306 --> 00:55:13.685 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>We must rewild the world.</i>

568
00:55:13.768 --> 00:55:16.146 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[uplifting music playing]

569
00:55:16.229 --> 00:55:17.856 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[reindeer grunting]

570
00:55:20.316 --> 00:55:22.235 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[birds hooting]

571
00:55:30.827 --> 00:55:32.412 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[buffalo snorting]

572
00:55:38.543 --> 00:55:40.336 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[birds cawing]

573
00:55:45.175 --> 00:55:47.177 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[elephants trumpeting]

574
00:55:53.600 --> 00:55:57.520 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Rewilding the world is simpler
than you might think.

575
00:55:58.188 --> 00:55:59.898 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And the changes we have to make

576
00:55:59.981 --> 00:56:03.943 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
will only benefit ourselves
and the generations that follow.

577
00:56:05.111 --> 00:56:09.407 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
A century from now,
our planet could be a wild place again.

578
00:56:10.200 --> 00:56:12.077 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And I'm going to tell you how.

579
00:56:13.745 --> 00:56:16.081 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[cawing and chirping]

580
00:56:19.834 --> 00:56:25.757 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Every other species on Earth reaches</i>
<i>a maximum population after a time.</i>

581
00:56:27.133 --> 00:56:31.346 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>The number that can be sustained</i>
<i>on the natural resources available.</i>

582
00:56:34.265 --> 00:56:35.767 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>With nothing to restrict us,</i>

583
00:56:35.850 --> 00:56:40.188 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>our population has been growing</i>
<i>dramatically throughout my lifetime.</i>

584
00:56:40.271 --> 00:56:41.439 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[crowd chanting]

585
00:56:41.523 --> 00:56:43.149 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>On current projections,</i>

586
00:56:43.233 --> 00:56:48.947 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>there will be 11 billion people</i>
<i>on Earth by 2100.</i>

587
00:56:49.823 --> 00:56:51.616 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>But it's possible to slow,</i>

588
00:56:51.699 --> 00:56:56.996 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>even to stop population growth</i>
<i>well before it reaches that point.</i>

589
00:57:01.751 --> 00:57:03.711 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Japan's standard of living</i>

590
00:57:03.795 --> 00:57:07.382 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>climbed rapidly in the latter half</i>
<i>of the 20th century.</i>

591
00:57:08.675 --> 00:57:11.511 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>As healthcare and education improved,</i>

592
00:57:11.594 --> 00:57:15.098 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>people's expectations</i>
<i>and opportunities grew,</i>

593
00:57:15.181 --> 00:57:17.517 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>and the birth rate fell.</i>

594
00:57:19.144 --> 00:57:24.816 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>In 1950, a Japanese family was likely</i>
<i>to have three or more children.</i>

595
00:57:26.025 --> 00:57:29.988 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>By 1975, the average was two.</i>

596
00:57:33.116 --> 00:57:36.744 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>The result is that the population</i>
<i>has now stabilized</i>

597
00:57:36.828 --> 00:57:40.039 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>and has hardly changed</i>
<i>since the millennium.</i>

598
00:57:41.916 --> 00:57:45.795 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>There are signs that this has started</i>
<i>to happen across the globe.</i>

599
00:57:48.548 --> 00:57:53.136 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>As nations develop everywhere,</i>
<i>people choose to have fewer children.</i>

600
00:57:57.557 --> 00:58:00.935 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>The number of children being born</i>
<i>worldwide every year</i>

601
00:58:01.519 --> 00:58:03.646 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>is about to level off.</i>

602
00:58:05.732 --> 00:58:08.276 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>A key reason the population</i>
<i>is still growing</i>

603
00:58:08.902 --> 00:58:10.904 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>is because many of us are living longer.</i>

604
00:58:13.531 --> 00:58:15.200 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>At some point in the future,</i>

605
00:58:15.700 --> 00:58:19.913 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>the human population will peak</i>
<i>for the very first time.</i>

606
00:58:21.164 --> 00:58:22.665 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>The sooner it happens,</i>

607
00:58:22.749 --> 00:58:26.336 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>the easier it makes everything else</i>
<i>we have to do.</i>

608
00:58:26.419 --> 00:58:28.338 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[crowd cheering]

609
00:58:30.715 --> 00:58:33.676 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Attenborough] <i>By working hard</i>
<i>to raise people out of poverty,</i>

610
00:58:34.385 --> 00:58:37.096 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>giving all access to healthcare,</i>

611
00:58:37.764 --> 00:58:42.560 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>and enabling girls in particular</i>
<i>to stay in school as long as possible,</i>

612
00:58:42.644 --> 00:58:46.731 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>we can make it peak sooner</i>
<i>and at a lower level.</i>

613
00:58:48.566 --> 00:58:51.027 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why wouldn't we want to do these things?

614
00:58:51.110 --> 00:58:53.238 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Giving people
a greater opportunity of life

615
00:58:53.321 --> 00:58:55.448 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
is what we would want to do anyway.

616
00:58:56.115 --> 00:59:00.286 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The trick is to raise
the standard of living around the world

617
00:59:00.370 --> 00:59:03.831 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
without increasing
our impact on that world.

618
00:59:03.915 --> 00:59:05.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That may sound impossible,

619
00:59:05.583 --> 00:59:08.336 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but there are ways
in which we can do this.

620
00:59:17.762 --> 00:59:21.558 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>The living world</i>
<i>is essentially solar-powered.</i>

621
00:59:24.185 --> 00:59:25.728 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>The earth's plants</i>

622
00:59:25.812 --> 00:59:30.817 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>capture three trillion kilowatt-hours</i>
<i>of solar energy each day.</i>

623
00:59:30.900 --> 00:59:32.068 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[birds chirping]

624
00:59:32.151 --> 00:59:38.199 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>That's almost 20 times the energy</i>
<i>we need... just from sunlight.</i>

625
00:59:42.704 --> 00:59:46.040 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Imagine if we phase out fossil fuels</i>

626
00:59:46.624 --> 00:59:51.504 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>and run our world on the eternal energies</i>
<i>of nature too.</i>

627
00:59:52.505 --> 00:59:57.594 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Sunlight, wind, water and geothermal.</i>

628
01:00:00.555 --> 01:00:02.557 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[indistinct chatter]

629
01:00:03.933 --> 01:00:05.852 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Attenborough] <i>At the turn of the century,</i>

630
01:00:05.935 --> 01:00:11.858 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Morocco relied on imported oil and gas</i>
<i>for almost all of its energy.</i>

631
01:00:12.692 --> 01:00:16.613 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Today, it generates</i>
<i>40% of its needs at home</i>

632
01:00:17.363 --> 01:00:23.995 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>from a network of renewable power plants,</i>
<i>including the world's largest solar farm.</i>

633
01:00:27.999 --> 01:00:29.626 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Sitting on the edge of the Sahara,</i>

634
01:00:30.710 --> 01:00:33.338 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>and cabled directly into southern Europe,</i>

635
01:00:33.921 --> 01:00:40.345 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Morocco could be an exporter</i>
<i>of solar energy by 2050.</i>

636
01:00:47.101 --> 01:00:53.816 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Within 20 years, renewables are predicted</i>
<i>to be the world's main source of power.</i>

637
01:00:55.151 --> 01:00:58.071 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>But we can make them the only source.</i>

638
01:00:59.030 --> 01:01:05.411 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's crazy that our banks and our pensions
are investing in fossil fuel...

639
01:01:06.371 --> 01:01:08.164 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
when these are the very things

640
01:01:08.247 --> 01:01:11.876 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that are jeopardizing the future
that we are saving for.

641
01:01:12.377 --> 01:01:13.961 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sirens wailing]

642
01:01:14.629 --> 01:01:18.132 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>A renewable future</i>
<i>will be full of benefits.</i>

643
01:01:18.883 --> 01:01:22.095 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Energy everywhere will be more affordable.</i>

644
01:01:23.388 --> 01:01:26.391 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Our cities will be cleaner and quieter.</i>

645
01:01:27.600 --> 01:01:30.770 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>And renewable energy will never run out.</i>

646
01:01:46.285 --> 01:01:51.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>The living world can't operate without</i>
<i>a healthy ocean and neither can we.</i>

647
01:01:58.464 --> 01:02:03.553 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>The ocean is a critical ally in our battle</i>
<i>to reduce carbon in the atmosphere.</i>

648
01:02:06.514 --> 01:02:10.893 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>The more diverse it is,</i>
<i>the better it does that job.</i>

649
01:02:14.397 --> 01:02:15.606 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[whales singing]

650
01:02:28.453 --> 01:02:34.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>And, of course, the ocean is important</i>
<i>to all of us as a source of food.</i>

651
01:02:36.878 --> 01:02:40.256 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Fishing is world's greatest wild harvest.</i>

652
01:02:40.339 --> 01:02:43.634 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>And if we do it right, it can continue...</i>

653
01:02:44.719 --> 01:02:48.097 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>because there's a win-win at play.</i>

654
01:02:49.098 --> 01:02:51.142 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>The healthier the marine habitat,</i>

655
01:02:51.225 --> 01:02:55.188 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>the more fish there will be,</i>
<i>and the more there will be to eat.</i>

656
01:03:02.653 --> 01:03:06.365 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Palau is a Pacific Island nation</i>

657
01:03:06.449 --> 01:03:11.287 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>reliant on its coral reefs</i>
<i>for fish and tourism.</i>

658
01:03:15.500 --> 01:03:17.835 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>When fish stocks began to reduce,</i>

659
01:03:17.919 --> 01:03:22.089 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>the Palauans responded</i>
<i>by restricting fishing practices</i>

660
01:03:22.173 --> 01:03:26.010 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>and banning fishing</i>
<i>entirely from many areas.</i>

661
01:03:29.263 --> 01:03:33.059 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Protected fish populations</i>
<i>soon became so healthy,</i>

662
01:03:33.142 --> 01:03:36.729 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>they spilt over into the areas</i>
<i>open to fishing.</i>

663
01:03:42.318 --> 01:03:43.361 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>As a result,</i>

664
01:03:43.444 --> 01:03:47.698 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>the "no fish" zones have increased</i>
<i>the catch of the local fishermen,</i>

665
01:03:47.782 --> 01:03:51.953 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>while at the same time</i>
<i>allowing the reefs to recover.</i>

666
01:03:56.833 --> 01:04:01.462 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Imagine if we committed to</i>
<i>a similar approach across the world.</i>

667
01:04:02.505 --> 01:04:07.635 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Estimates suggest that "no fish" zones</i>
<i>over a third of our coastal seas</i>

668
01:04:07.718 --> 01:04:12.557 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>would be sufficient to provide us</i>
<i>with all the fish we will ever need.</i>

669
01:04:18.271 --> 01:04:20.147 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>In international waters,</i>

670
01:04:20.231 --> 01:04:25.862 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>the UN is attempting to create</i>
<i>the biggest "no fish" zone of all.</i>

671
01:04:28.072 --> 01:04:31.742 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>In one act,</i>
<i>this would transform the open ocean</i>

672
01:04:31.826 --> 01:04:35.621 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>from a place exhausted</i>
<i>by subsidized fishing fleets</i>

673
01:04:36.205 --> 01:04:41.419 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>to a wilderness that will help us all</i>
<i>in our efforts to combat climate change.</i>

674
01:04:43.087 --> 01:04:45.798 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>The world's greatest wildlife reserve.</i>

675
01:05:02.440 --> 01:05:04.525 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>When it comes to the land,</i>

676
01:05:04.609 --> 01:05:08.279 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
we must radically reduce the area
we use to farm,

677
01:05:08.362 --> 01:05:11.198 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
so that we can make space
for returning wilderness.

678
01:05:11.282 --> 01:05:16.329 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And the quickest and most effective way
to do that is for us to change our diet.

679
01:05:17.038 --> 01:05:19.081 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[birds chirping]

680
01:05:22.001 --> 01:05:24.670 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Large carnivores are rare in nature</i>

681
01:05:24.754 --> 01:05:28.424 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>because it takes a lot of prey</i>
<i>to support each of them.</i>

682
01:05:29.133 --> 01:05:31.135 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[wildebeest snorting]

683
01:05:35.097 --> 01:05:38.184 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>For every single predator</i>
<i>on the Serengeti,</i>

684
01:05:38.267 --> 01:05:41.354 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>there are more than 100 prey animals.</i>

685
01:05:41.437 --> 01:05:43.439 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[snorting]

686
01:05:45.775 --> 01:05:47.735 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Whenever we choose a piece of meat,</i>

687
01:05:47.818 --> 01:05:52.949 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>we too are unwittingly demanding</i>
<i>a huge expanse of space.</i>

688
01:05:57.828 --> 01:06:02.875 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The planet can't support
billions of large meat-eaters.

689
01:06:03.376 --> 01:06:05.127 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
There just isn't the space.

690
01:06:05.628 --> 01:06:06.587 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[dings]

691
01:06:09.674 --> 01:06:12.760 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>If we all had a largely plant-based diet,</i>

692
01:06:13.761 --> 01:06:17.556 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>we would need only half the land</i>
<i>we use at the moment.</i>

693
01:06:19.141 --> 01:06:23.145 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And because we would be
then dedicated to raising plants,

694
01:06:23.229 --> 01:06:27.024 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
we could increase the yield
of this land substantially.

695
01:06:32.863 --> 01:06:37.952 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>The Netherlands is one of the world's</i>
<i>most densely-populated countries.</i>

696
01:06:39.203 --> 01:06:44.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>It's covered with small family-run farms</i>
<i>with no room for expansion.</i>

697
01:06:47.294 --> 01:06:52.842 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>So, Dutch farmers have become expert</i>
<i>at getting the most out of every hectare.</i>

698
01:06:55.636 --> 01:06:58.889 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Increasingly,</i>
<i>they're doing so sustainably.</i>

699
01:07:02.184 --> 01:07:08.441 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Raising yields tenfold in two generations</i>
<i>while at the same time using less water,</i>

700
01:07:09.108 --> 01:07:14.697 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>fewer pesticides, less fertilizer</i>
<i>and emitting less carbon.</i>

701
01:07:19.493 --> 01:07:20.703 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Despite its size,</i>

702
01:07:20.786 --> 01:07:26.250 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>the Netherlands is now the world's</i>
<i>second largest exporter of food.</i>

703
01:07:30.796 --> 01:07:36.761 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's entirely possible for us to apply
both low-tech and hi-tech solutions

704
01:07:36.844 --> 01:07:40.514 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to produce much more food
from much less land.

705
01:07:42.725 --> 01:07:46.312 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>We can start to produce food</i>
<i>in new spaces.</i>

706
01:07:48.773 --> 01:07:51.692 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Indoors, within cities.</i>

707
01:07:55.029 --> 01:07:58.365 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Even in places</i>
<i>where there's no land at all.</i>

708
01:08:12.088 --> 01:08:14.548 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>As we improve our approach to farming,</i>

709
01:08:14.632 --> 01:08:18.761 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
we'll start to reverse the land-grab
that we've been pursuing

710
01:08:18.844 --> 01:08:20.930 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
ever since we began to farm,

711
01:08:21.639 --> 01:08:27.728 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
which is essential because we have
an urgent need for all that free land.

712
01:08:34.944 --> 01:08:39.990 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Forests are a fundamental component</i>
<i>of our planet's recovery.</i>

713
01:08:41.617 --> 01:08:46.330 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>They are the best technology nature has</i>
<i>for locking away carbon.</i>

714
01:08:48.082 --> 01:08:51.001 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>And they are centers of biodiversity.</i>

715
01:08:55.172 --> 01:08:58.175 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Again, the two features work together.</i>

716
01:08:58.717 --> 01:09:01.804 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>The wilder and more diverse forests are,</i>

717
01:09:01.887 --> 01:09:06.350 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>the more effective they are</i>
<i>at absorbing carbon from the atmosphere.</i>

718
01:09:08.018 --> 01:09:12.773 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We must immediately
halt deforestation everywhere...

719
01:09:13.649 --> 01:09:20.322 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>and grow crops like oil palm and soya</i>
<i>only on land that was deforested long ago.</i>

720
01:09:21.448 --> 01:09:24.118 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>After all, there's plenty of it.</i>

721
01:09:26.287 --> 01:09:28.414 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But we can do better than that.

722
01:09:32.042 --> 01:09:37.756 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>A century ago, more than three quarters</i>
<i>of Costa Rica was covered with forest.</i>

723
01:09:45.472 --> 01:09:51.729 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>By the 1980s, uncontrolled logging</i>
<i>had reduced this to just one quarter.</i>

724
01:09:54.607 --> 01:09:56.567 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>The government decided to act,</i>

725
01:09:56.650 --> 01:10:01.572 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>offering grants to land owners</i>
<i>to replant native trees.</i>

726
01:10:06.035 --> 01:10:08.162 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>In just 25 years,</i>

727
01:10:08.245 --> 01:10:13.626 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>the forest has returned to cover</i>
<i>half of Costa Rica once again.</i>

728
01:10:14.293 --> 01:10:16.420 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[birds chirping]

729
01:10:18.881 --> 01:10:23.093 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Just imagine if we achieve this</i>
<i>on a global scale.</i>

730
01:10:25.804 --> 01:10:28.140 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The return of the trees would absorb

731
01:10:28.224 --> 01:10:31.310 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
as much as two thirds
of the carbon emissions

732
01:10:31.393 --> 01:10:35.522 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that have been pumped into the atmosphere
by our activities to date.

733
01:10:43.113 --> 01:10:44.823 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>With all these things,</i>

734
01:10:45.407 --> 01:10:48.077 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>there is one overriding principle.</i>

735
01:10:50.996 --> 01:10:56.335 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Nature is our biggest ally</i>
<i>and our greatest inspiration.</i>

736
01:10:58.671 --> 01:11:02.675 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>We just have to do what nature</i>
<i>has always done.</i>

737
01:11:04.301 --> 01:11:08.555 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>It worked out the secret of life long ago.</i>

738
01:11:14.436 --> 01:11:18.440 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>In this world,</i>
<i>a species can only thrive...</i>

739
01:11:19.858 --> 01:11:23.862 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>when everything else</i>
<i>around it thrives, too.</i>

740
01:11:29.827 --> 01:11:32.663 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>We can solve the problems we now face</i>

741
01:11:32.746 --> 01:11:35.708 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>by embracing this reality.</i>

742
01:11:38.377 --> 01:11:40.796 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>If we take care of nature,</i>

743
01:11:42.298 --> 01:11:45.301 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>nature will take care of us.</i>

744
01:11:48.095 --> 01:11:53.475 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>It's now time for our species</i>
<i>to stop simply growing.</i>

745
01:11:55.436 --> 01:12:00.774 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>To establish a life on our planet</i>
<i>in balance with nature.</i>

746
01:12:03.610 --> 01:12:06.113 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>To start to thrive.</i>

747
01:12:09.533 --> 01:12:13.370 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
When you think about it,
we're completing a journey.

748
01:12:14.913 --> 01:12:18.000 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Ten thousand years ago,
as hunter-gatherers,

749
01:12:18.709 --> 01:12:23.047 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
we lived a sustainable life
because that was the only option.

750
01:12:24.089 --> 01:12:29.553 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
All these years later,
it's once again the only option.

751
01:12:29.636 --> 01:12:31.930 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We need to rediscover...

752
01:12:33.015 --> 01:12:34.641 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
how to be sustainable.

753
01:12:34.725 --> 01:12:38.645 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
To move from being apart from nature

754
01:12:38.729 --> 01:12:43.317 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
to becoming a part of nature once again.

755
01:12:48.447 --> 01:12:51.325 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Tonight, we've got
a rather different program for you.

756
01:12:54.203 --> 01:12:57.456 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Attenborough] <i>If we can change</i>
<i>the way we live on Earth,</i>

757
01:12:58.457 --> 01:13:01.293 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>an alternative future comes into view.</i>

758
01:13:04.880 --> 01:13:06.382 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>In this future,</i>

759
01:13:06.965 --> 01:13:13.430 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>we discover ways to benefit from our land</i>
<i>that help, rather than hinder, wilderness.</i>

760
01:13:15.140 --> 01:13:21.105 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Ways to fish our seas that enable them</i>
<i>to come quickly back to life.</i>

761
01:13:27.694 --> 01:13:32.199 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>And ways to harvest</i>
<i>our forests sustainably.</i>

762
01:13:35.828 --> 01:13:42.584 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>We will finally learn how to work</i>
<i>with nature rather than against it.</i>

763
01:13:45.254 --> 01:13:49.716 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
In the end, after a lifetime's exploration
of the living world,

764
01:13:49.800 --> 01:13:52.094 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm certain of one thing.

765
01:13:53.011 --> 01:13:55.973 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This is not about saving our planet...

766
01:13:56.849 --> 01:13:59.435 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
it's about saving ourselves.

767
01:14:04.189 --> 01:14:10.529 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>The truth is, with or without us,</i>
<i>the natural world will rebuild.</i>

768
01:14:20.456 --> 01:14:24.710 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>In the 30 years</i>
<i>since the evacuation of Chernobyl,</i>

769
01:14:25.377 --> 01:14:29.006 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>the wild has reclaimed the space.</i>

770
01:14:29.089 --> 01:14:30.924 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[birds chirping]

771
01:14:40.267 --> 01:14:44.354 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Today, the forest has taken over the city.</i>

772
01:14:58.285 --> 01:15:02.998 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>It's a sanctuary for wild animals</i>
<i>that are very rare elsewhere.</i>

773
01:15:09.713 --> 01:15:14.760 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>And powerful evidence</i>
<i>that however grave our mistakes,</i>

774
01:15:14.843 --> 01:15:18.222 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>nature will ultimately overcome them.</i>

775
01:15:22.726 --> 01:15:25.604 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>The living world will endure.</i>

776
01:15:27.648 --> 01:15:31.401 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>We humans cannot presume the same.</i>

777
01:15:34.238 --> 01:15:35.781 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>We've come this far</i>

778
01:15:35.864 --> 01:15:39.701 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>because we are the smartest creatures</i>
<i>that have ever lived.</i>

779
01:15:44.456 --> 01:15:49.169 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>But to continue,</i>
<i>we require more than intelligence.</i>

780
01:15:51.213 --> 01:15:53.966 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>We require wisdom.</i>

781
01:16:07.437 --> 01:16:11.900 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There are many differences between humans
and the rest of the species on earth,

782
01:16:12.484 --> 01:16:17.781 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but one that has been expressed is that
we alone are able to imagine the future.

783
01:16:19.116 --> 01:16:23.078 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
For a long time, I and perhaps you
have dreaded that future.

784
01:16:24.079 --> 01:16:28.667 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But it's now becoming apparent
that it's not all doom and gloom.

785
01:16:29.751 --> 01:16:32.170 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
There's a chance for us to make amends,

786
01:16:32.921 --> 01:16:36.633 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to complete our journey of development,
manage our impact,

787
01:16:36.717 --> 01:16:41.388 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and once again become a species
in balance with nature.

788
01:16:42.472 --> 01:16:45.225 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All we need is the will to do so.

789
01:16:45.726 --> 01:16:50.606 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We now have the opportunity to create
the perfect home for ourselves,

790
01:16:51.148 --> 01:16:57.195 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and restore the rich, healthy,
and wonderful world that we inherited.

791
01:16:58.530 --> 01:17:00.032 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Just imagine that.

